content:
The Commercial line of business gives you a fully functional example of the Commercial Auto product models, rating procedures, and business processes for quoting and issuing policies.

You can use the models and processes as a reference to develop your own product models and business processes or extend them and make them your own.

Product Model: Commercial Auto
Rating Procedure: CommercialAutoRating

The product model provides the structure for the data JSON that moves through the business processes. The Commercial Auto product model is single-instance, which means that customers can insure only one business per policy. All coverages have been designed to be configured at the policy level.

To learn more about the product model, see Commercial Auto Product Model.
The rating procedures take information from the prospective customer and calculate prices for coverages, then the product model rating simulation rolls up those prices and calculates the total premium.

To learn more about these rating procedures, see Commercial Auto Rating.

Business Processes

This process guides prospective customers to get a rated quote for a business product:

Quote Business Process

The Commercial Auto Product Model is a single-instance product model that lets businesses create quotes for multiple vehicles tied to a single location.
Auto Attribute Catalog lists all attributes used for the Auto line of business by Attribute Category.
Commercial Auto Rating uses the product model data, product rating procedure, and pricing formulas to price coverages, vehicles, and total premium.
Commercial Quote Business Process can be used as an example or extended to create own business processes.
title: Commercial Auto Insurance Overview
